name: Due Leoni Venice Luxury Apartment
description:
The ULTIMATE in refinement and elegant living, with views that must surely be second to none!

Directly overlooking St. Mark’s Basilica, St. Mark’s Square and the Campanile towering tall, it’s with barely contained excitement that we welcome Due Leoni…

… A property that made us all gasp in astonishment, to describe it as ‘stunning’ would be an understatement to say the least!

The space
Hosting 6 astute guests in trip-of-a-lifetime surroundings and (almost!) rubbing shoulders with the Torre dell’ Orologio (Clock Tower) next door, the 4 bedroom Due Leoni is as rare as it is ravishing and is bright, uplifting and exceptional throughout.

Classically furnished with grace and panache and on the 4th floor served by lift, the air-conditioned* apartment boasts gorgeous wooden parquet flooring while its walls are adorned with period paintings and prints.

‘Take-your-breath-away-wonderful’ and including Wi-Fi, the accommodation c
neighborhood_overview:
OUR COMMENT

100% Chic and entirely unique - one of the most remarkable rental properties in Venice today.

Standing in the iconic beating heart of ‘La Serenissima’ - St. Mark’s Square - where, at night, the orchestras of the world-famous Gran Caffe Quadri and Caffe Florian conjure up a truly magical atmosphere (music is dependent on weather and season!), while the pink and white marble of the Doge’s Palace glows, and the mosaics of the Basilica shimmer in the darkness.

A short stroll to the recently restored Rialto Bridge crossing the Grand Canal, and T Fondaco Dei Tedeschi - Venice’s new lifestyle department store.

Also within easy reach of 2 well-stocked supermarkets for all your self-catering requirements - one at Salizada San Lio and the other at Rialto - and to the vaporetto (water bus) stops at San Zaccaria and Vallaresso for simple and convenient travel around town.
host_about:
I'm co-founder and director of Views on Venice and I have over 20 years experience in the short and luxury rents market in Veneto.
I grew up in the fifteenth-century palace of my family on the Grand Canal, where I live today with my young family.
My loves include travel, scuba diving, good wine ... and Venice!



Sono co-fondatore e direttore di Views on Venice ed ho un'esperienza di oltre 20 anni nel mercato degli affitti brevi e degli affitti di lusso in Veneto.
Sono cresciuto all'interno del palazzo quattrocentesco della mia famiglia sul Canal Grande, dove vivo oggi con la mia giovane famiglia.
I miei amori comprendono viaggi, immersioni subacquee, buon vino ... e Venezia!

name: Capannone Redentore
description:
… A wonderful wood-enrobed warehouse conversion and, to the best of our knowledge, the only privately owned property in Venice’s historical centre fortunate enough to feature an indoor swimming pool of this size.

The space
Ease into the Venice lifestyle like a duck takes to water in this remarkable new property with its own indoor pool!

Thought to have started life as a warehouse belonging to the monastery of the Capuchin monks of the Redentore during the time of the Serenissima Republic of Venice, and now transformed into a strikingly unique yet quietly luxurious living and leisure space, this stylish conversion sleeps up to 6 guests in 3 bedroomed accommodation surrounding the pool.

Visible in a number of paintings and engravings of the Redentore by artists including Canaletto and Guardi, and reinvented with exceptional originality and the utmost respect for the materials used in its original construction – think gorgeous bare brickwork an
neighborhood_overview:
A delightful waterside amble to Harry’s Dolci for a spot of refined summertime canal-side dining beneath bright white canopies, to the Hilton Molino Stucky’s Aromi and Bacaromi restaurants and Skyline Rooftop Bar with its sweeping panoramic views of Venice across the glittering Giudecca Canal, and to the showroom of the historic Fortuny factory close by.

Near to a host of small local shops for all your self-catering needs - including a Prix supermarket near Redentore and a Coop supermarket near Palanca – and to a variety of traditional bars and restaurants including the well-regarded Ai Cacciatore, La Palanca and the family-run Altanella with its pretty outdoor terrace.

neighborhood_overview:
L'appartamento si trova in Calle del Paradiso, nel sestiere di San Polo, il più piccolo sestiere della città, ma di certo il più ricco di storia, cultura e arte.
Il mercato del sestiere ebbe la sua prima collocazione proprio in calle del Paradiso, dove si ha testimonianza che fin dalla fine del primo secolo del 1000 numerose erano le botteghe ed i magazzini; un piccolo nucleo che poi diventerà agli inizi del 1200 il mercato della città.
Ogni tanto, passeggiando per le calli di Venezia, ci si imbatte in strutture lignee che sporgono dai palazzi: si tratta dei Barbacani.
Sono travature in legno utilizzate per sorreggere le strutture aggettanti degli edifici con lo scopo di guadagnare spazio – permettevano di allargare solo i piani superiori delle case - senza invadere le strette calli veneziane.

I spent most part of my life studying nature, which is a very passion. Graduated in Natural Sciences I am a tourist guide leading people through the Venetian lagoon, a very wide ecosystem.
 I like traveling whenever I can and knowing new people and other cultures is my must. That's why I decided to be a (Website hidden by Airbnb) is a way to travel without moving.
I learnt English and French in two specific and curious ways. My English comes from another real passion, the American Football, for which I have been playing since 20 years. 
I improved my french doing voluntarism in Africa, so becoming a France-Afrique speaking.
I would be very happy to show you the city and its surroundings, making you living the Venetian experience and tasting the differences from the other cities in the world. So, not only the greatest Saint Mark's square, but you will enjoy the cuisine, the Venetian sounds, the mainland and the lagoon as (Website hidden by Airbnb) what do you think to sky in the Dolomites mountains(i.e. in Cortina) and sleeping in downtown Venice at the same time...if you are imaging, the most part is done!

Sono laureato in Scienze naturali e per molti anni ho lavorato nel turismo come guida naturalistica facendo scoprire alle persone la mia amata terra e in particolare la laguna di Venezia. Amo viaggiare e vorrei farlo molto di più per poter incontrare e conoscere persone che vivono in modo molto di verso da me. Per queste ragioni ho pensato di diventare host, per riassaporare le piacevoli sensazioni della scoperta e del far scoprire. Insomma viaggiare rimanendo fermi!
Ho giocato a football americano per vent'anni con cui ho imparato l'inglese che conosco, ho fatto molto volontariato sia in Italia che in Africa dove ho affinato il mio francese....ora divenuto france-afrique!
Sarò lieto anche di mostrarvi la città e i suoi dintorni vivendola come la vive un veneziano, assaporandone le enormi differenze e contraddizioni che la rendono unica. Quindi non solo la splendida Piazza San Marco, ma anche la cucina, il vino, la musica, la terraferma e la laguna.......e che ne dite di sciare a Cortina e dormire in centro storico? Si può fare!

A scenographic staircase leads to the kitchen, at a twi
neighborhood_overview:
The District (Dorsoduro)
Dorsoduro is one of the most exclusive districts of the romantic city of Venice, hosting in zone of the Accademia and Zattere, unique and ancient examples of residential architecture in Venice.
Dorsoduro offers to those who has passion for history of art, numerous opportunities to discover the history of Venice, impregnated in the same walls that form the lagoon city ..
A short distance from the famous Accademia Bridge, you can visit the Museum of Ca' Rezzonico Eighteenth Century. It was originally commissioned by the patrician scholar Filippo Bon, who entrusted the project to Baldassarre Longhena. Following the residential palace passed to the Rezzonico family who enlarged it, adding rooms individually decorated with fine frescoes.
Other historical sites equal for interest and beauty are the Accademia Gallery, the ancient sources and unique in the world illustrating the history of Venetian painting from the fourteenth to the eighteenth
